1
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:30,340
Hello.

2
00:01:30,340 --> 00:01:31,500
Half or full portion

3
00:01:31,500 --> 00:01:32,900
of white cut chicken?

4
00:01:32,900 --> 00:01:33,620
Full, please.

5
00:01:33,620 --> 00:01:34,280
Got it.

6
00:01:34,420 --> 00:01:36,099
And we'll also have

7
00:01:36,379 --> 00:01:38,040
the typhoon shelter fried crab.

8
00:01:38,340 --> 00:01:39,299
- Okay.
- And the steamed fish.

9
00:01:39,540 --> 00:01:40,060
Sure thing.

10
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:40,780
Here you go.

11
00:01:40,780 --> 00:01:41,780
Anything else you want?

12
00:01:42,379 --> 00:01:43,099
That's enough.

13
00:01:43,200 --> 00:01:44,099
No point wasting food.

14
00:01:45,719 --> 00:01:46,200
Okay.

15
00:01:47,780 --> 00:01:48,239
Oh right,

16
00:01:49,239 --> 00:01:49,879
when you and Ding Lei

17
00:01:49,879 --> 00:01:50,980
went to get the confirmations,

18
00:01:51,239 --> 00:01:52,000
did you pull the list?

19
00:01:52,879 --> 00:01:53,819
I've already done it.

20
00:01:53,900 --> 00:01:55,560
It's in my office drawer.

21
00:01:56,980 --> 00:01:58,099
Haoyun's financial accounts

22
00:01:58,099 --> 00:01:59,120
are all with local banks.

23
00:01:59,939 --> 00:02:00,819
Check out

24
00:02:00,819 --> 00:02:01,420
the local policies later.

25
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:02,500
After all,

26
00:02:02,500 --> 00:02:03,540
those little details

27
00:02:03,879 --> 00:02:04,859
are easy to tamper with.

28
00:02:05,519 --> 00:02:06,060
Okay.

29
00:02:24,520 --> 00:02:25,060
Excuse me.

30
00:02:26,919 --> 00:02:27,759
All your dishes are served.

31
00:02:27,840 --> 00:02:28,419
Enjoy.

32
00:02:28,500 --> 00:02:29,199
This spread's plenty for us.

33
00:02:29,599 --> 00:02:30,219
This is good.

34
00:02:30,419 --> 00:02:31,099
Sweet,

35
00:02:31,219 --> 00:02:31,740
your favorite.

36
00:02:34,699 --> 00:02:35,939
You two are so close?

37
00:02:36,599 --> 00:02:37,379
I never heard

38
00:02:37,379 --> 00:02:38,219
Miao Jing mention you.

39
00:02:39,300 --> 00:02:40,159
Does your company

40
00:02:40,159 --> 00:02:41,219
require staff

41
00:02:41,219 --> 00:02:42,560
to report family info on hiring?

42
00:02:43,159 --> 00:02:43,939
No, not really.

43
00:02:44,460 --> 00:02:45,099
No surprise

44
00:02:45,099 --> 00:02:46,419
she never brought me up

45
00:02:46,639 --> 00:02:47,159
to you.

46
00:02:49,360 --> 00:02:50,800
Workplace lines don't call for that.

47
00:02:51,080 --> 00:02:53,659
But besides work,

48
00:02:54,419 --> 00:02:55,860
we used to date.

49
00:03:00,740 --> 00:03:01,939
She's quite reserved.

50
00:03:02,900 --> 00:03:03,620
If we didn't work

51
00:03:03,620 --> 00:03:04,939
at the same firm,

52
00:03:05,639 --> 00:03:07,139
we'd lose touch completely,

53
00:03:07,500 --> 00:03:08,400
like her last ex.

54
00:03:13,300 --> 00:03:14,000
There was someone before him?

55
00:03:15,599 --> 00:03:18,039
I remember it was her college classmate.

56
00:03:18,360 --> 00:03:19,300
They met on the swim team.

57
00:03:23,439 --> 00:03:24,620
We just weren't compatible.

58
00:03:25,979 --> 00:03:27,300
Even her first love ended that bitterly.

59
00:03:28,180 --> 00:03:28,979
I guess I only get to see her

60
00:03:28,979 --> 00:03:29,900
thanks to our jobs.

61
00:03:32,939 --> 00:03:33,620
First love?

62
00:03:34,659 --> 00:03:35,360
I doubt it.

63
00:03:38,620 --> 00:03:39,780
Let's eat.

64
00:03:39,780 --> 00:03:41,620
It'll get cold.

65
00:03:44,139 --> 00:03:45,500
Help yourself, my treat.

66
00:04:03,120 --> 00:04:04,620
Check, table 28 please.

67
00:04:06,159 --> 00:04:07,080
Someone left a card

68
00:04:07,080 --> 00:04:09,240
for your table.

69
00:04:09,819 --> 00:04:11,759
The guy with glasses.

70
00:04:11,860 --> 00:04:12,680
That's my card.

71
00:04:12,840 --> 00:04:13,560
Just swipe it.

72
00:04:17,379 --> 00:04:18,259
She's in the restroom.

73
00:04:21,519 --> 00:04:22,560
You're our guest.

74
00:04:23,079 --> 00:04:24,600
Guests should be treated.

75
00:04:25,720 --> 00:04:27,199
I said I'd treat her anyway.

76
00:04:27,439 --> 00:04:29,000
No way the guest foots the bill.

77
00:04:31,079 --> 00:04:32,920
Want another table

78
00:04:32,920 --> 00:04:34,480
to sort this out?

79
00:04:34,560 --> 00:04:35,379
What did you say?

80
00:04:37,220 --> 00:04:37,879
Your total is

81
00:04:37,879 --> 00:04:38,959
458 RMB.

82
00:04:41,740 --> 00:04:42,779
Just swipe the card, okay?

83
00:04:43,220 --> 00:04:44,180
Thanks.

84
00:04:54,920 --> 00:04:55,959
Let's drive you back.

85
00:04:56,139 --> 00:04:56,560
No need.

86
00:04:56,860 --> 00:04:57,579
My ride's almost here.

87
00:04:58,300 --> 00:04:58,980
Safe trip.

88
00:04:59,399 --> 00:05:00,240
See you tomorrow.

89
00:06:20,319 --> 00:06:21,139
What are you laughing at?

90
00:06:23,500 --> 00:06:24,639
I thought you'd ignore me

91
00:06:24,639 --> 00:06:25,480
till you got home.

92
00:06:28,180 --> 00:06:29,000
I wasn't ignoring you.

93
00:06:31,120 --> 00:06:32,279
You don't like Cen Ye.

94
00:06:35,480 --> 00:06:36,180
I barely know him.

95
00:06:36,519 --> 00:06:37,459
No strong feelings either way.

96
00:06:39,699 --> 00:06:40,959
I thought

97
00:06:40,980 --> 00:06:41,779
you'd want to hear

98
00:06:41,779 --> 00:06:43,160
about my past with him.

99
00:06:44,980 --> 00:06:45,660
But you think

100
00:06:46,459 --> 00:06:47,980
prying about exes

101
00:06:47,980 --> 00:06:48,680
is tacky

102
00:06:49,100 --> 00:06:50,839
and petty.

103
00:06:51,740 --> 00:06:52,639
So all you can do

104
00:06:52,639 --> 00:06:55,079
is toss and turn alone,

105
00:06:55,180 --> 00:06:56,399
your mind tangled

106
00:06:56,519 --> 00:06:57,759
in endless

107
00:06:57,839 --> 00:06:59,360
chaotic thoughts.

108
00:06:59,759 --> 00:07:00,120
And...

109
00:07:00,120 --> 00:07:01,839
A top grad from Jiaohai University,

110
00:07:01,839 --> 00:07:02,879
yet messes up idioms.

111
00:07:04,439 --> 00:07:05,839
Get huffy from embarrassment?

112
00:07:08,699 --> 00:07:10,040
I'm annoyed he knows more about

113
00:07:10,040 --> 00:07:11,040
your life these past years than I do.

114
00:07:15,959 --> 00:07:17,360
Well, he's an ex anyway.

115
00:07:24,420 --> 00:07:25,360
Tell me about

116
00:07:25,360 --> 00:07:26,319
your exes.

117
00:07:26,439 --> 00:07:27,279
I'm curious.

118
00:07:28,360 --> 00:07:28,879
What?

119
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:29,899
Nothing much to tell.

120
00:07:31,620 --> 00:07:33,139
I wanna know everything.

121
00:07:33,360 --> 00:07:34,639
When did you meet them,

122
00:07:34,639 --> 00:07:35,660
how many have there been,

123
00:07:36,660 --> 00:07:37,899
and what do they do?

124
00:07:38,120 --> 00:07:39,579
I met them ages ago.

125
00:07:39,699 --> 00:07:40,339
What?

126
00:07:40,699 --> 00:07:41,899
I met them ages ago.

127
00:07:42,319 --> 00:07:43,259
Go on, tell me.

128
00:07:49,939 --> 00:07:50,480
Come on in.

129
00:07:50,959 --> 00:07:51,579
I'll tell you.

130
00:08:10,100 --> 00:08:10,800
Look at all the dust.

131
00:08:18,279 --> 00:08:19,600
Why always pick plain ones like this?

132
00:08:19,759 --> 00:08:21,120
At least get something brighter.

133
00:08:22,199 --> 00:08:23,319
You wouldn't understand.

134
00:08:24,879 --> 00:08:26,040
Which one goes where?

135
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:27,120
Give me a hand.

136
00:08:28,139 --> 00:08:29,160
Your sister used to

137
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:30,699
have two pots of daisies

138
00:08:30,699 --> 00:08:32,320
on her desk.

139
00:08:32,960 --> 00:08:34,720
She loved that kind of color.

140
00:08:34,940 --> 00:08:35,679
Put that down.

141
00:08:36,440 --> 00:08:37,240
Start with this one.

142
00:08:41,559 --> 00:08:42,019
Okay.

143
00:09:07,779 --> 00:09:08,480
Almost done.

144
00:09:13,139 --> 00:09:13,720
Have some water.

145
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:24,480
How's business lately?

146
00:09:26,679 --> 00:09:27,200
Not bad.

147
00:09:27,799 --> 00:09:28,840
Not many kids,

148
00:09:29,299 --> 00:09:30,519
but more adults in the classes.

149
00:09:33,659 --> 00:09:34,820
Teaching adults

150
00:09:35,019 --> 00:09:36,559
is easier than kids anyway.

151
00:09:37,539 --> 00:09:38,360
Besides,

152
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:41,320
you're still a kid yourself.

153
00:09:41,940 --> 00:09:43,419
You don't have the patience for them.

154
00:09:54,200 --> 00:09:55,000
Heard

155
00:09:55,879 --> 00:09:56,340
you've been

156
00:09:56,340 --> 00:09:57,639
hanging around Zhang Bin a lot lately.

157
00:10:19,320 --> 00:10:20,440
Liu Binbo.

158
00:10:21,080 --> 00:10:21,740
You know him?

159
00:10:22,299 --> 00:10:22,879
Heard of him.

160
00:10:25,179 --> 00:10:26,000
He's from Gangcheng.

161
00:10:27,120 --> 00:10:28,919
Zhang Bin's been meeting with him

162
00:10:29,720 --> 00:10:30,679
to strike a big deal.

163
00:10:33,399 --> 00:10:34,759
What, exactly?

164
00:10:37,720 --> 00:10:39,259
Probably import and export business.

165
00:10:40,240 --> 00:10:41,080
Zhang Bin and I

166
00:10:41,299 --> 00:10:43,000
only play pool together occasionally.

167
00:10:43,500 --> 00:10:44,120
He wouldn't

168
00:10:44,120 --> 00:10:45,039
talk business with me.

169
00:10:54,419 --> 00:10:54,960
Leave this photo

170
00:10:54,960 --> 00:10:55,960
with us.

171
00:10:57,980 --> 00:10:58,840
Our police officers

172
00:11:00,179 --> 00:11:01,379
will keep an eye on Zhang Bin.

173
00:11:01,759 --> 00:11:03,080
Stay out of this.

174
00:11:03,340 --> 00:11:04,519
I'm just a regular citizen.

175
00:11:04,960 --> 00:11:05,720
What could I even do?

176
00:11:08,559 --> 00:11:09,139
Yi.

177
00:11:11,539 --> 00:11:12,580
Just a heads-up.

178
00:11:13,559 --> 00:11:15,080
Don't gamble your future

179
00:11:15,820 --> 00:11:17,360
on the past.

180
00:11:18,279 --> 00:11:18,799
It's not worth it.

181
00:11:19,879 --> 00:11:21,799
If we could let go that easily,

182
00:11:22,980 --> 00:11:23,860
then why

183
00:11:24,559 --> 00:11:25,639
did you bring me here today?

184
00:11:42,139 --> 00:11:43,240
Bo's moving tomorrow.

185
00:11:43,860 --> 00:11:44,919
I'm heading over to help them out.

186
00:11:45,539 --> 00:11:46,100
I'm off.

187
00:11:52,379 --> 00:11:52,940
Yi.

188
00:11:57,580 --> 00:11:58,879
Spare key's on the shoe cabinet.

189
00:11:59,679 --> 00:12:00,460
Take it with you.

190
00:12:21,740 --> 00:12:22,679
My princess.

191
00:12:22,759 --> 00:12:24,039
Check out our new place.

192
00:12:27,159 --> 00:12:28,159
It's spacious.

193
00:12:30,899 --> 00:12:31,440
This side

194
00:12:31,500 --> 00:12:32,080
faces

195
00:12:32,980 --> 00:12:33,580
south.

196
00:12:34,480 --> 00:12:35,120
What do you think?

197
00:12:37,659 --> 00:12:38,419
Check out the kitchen.

198
00:12:38,659 --> 00:12:39,460
Here?

199
00:12:39,620 --> 00:12:40,100
Yeah.

200
00:12:41,500 --> 00:12:42,659
Cookware's all ready.

201
00:12:42,759 --> 00:12:43,379
Everything's set.

202
00:12:43,379 --> 00:12:44,539
You've thought of everything.

203
00:12:44,559 --> 00:12:45,320
- Check out the room.
- There?

204
00:12:46,679 --> 00:12:47,360
Kids' room.

205
00:12:47,480 --> 00:12:47,860
Right.

206
00:12:50,480 --> 00:12:51,799
Bathroom's big too.

207
00:12:52,299 --> 00:12:53,000
Bedroom?

208
00:12:53,200 --> 00:12:54,039
Our bedroom.

209
00:12:55,639 --> 00:12:56,299
Like it?

210
00:13:01,200 --> 00:13:02,000
Yeah.

211
00:13:02,200 --> 00:13:03,080
I love it.

212
00:13:03,659 --> 00:13:04,379
Babe.

213
00:13:05,299 --> 00:13:06,100
Believe me.

214
00:13:07,519 --> 00:13:09,320
I'll give you a lifetime of happiness.

215
00:13:11,340 --> 00:13:11,919
Kang'an.

216
00:13:12,799 --> 00:13:13,679
Thank you for giving me

217
00:13:13,679 --> 00:13:14,860
such a warm home.

218
00:13:31,500 --> 00:13:32,360
Moving house

219
00:13:32,620 --> 00:13:33,200
Careful.

220
00:13:33,200 --> 00:13:34,559
ages you five years in one go.

221
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:38,120
That's what you get for not working out.

222
00:13:38,120 --> 00:13:39,279
Go clean the bedroom.

223
00:13:39,340 --> 00:13:39,940
Come on.

224
00:13:40,559 --> 00:13:42,000
Can't I at least get a sip of water?

225
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:43,120
My legs are killing me.

226
00:13:46,960 --> 00:13:48,639
Thanks for all the hassle, Yi.

227
00:13:48,779 --> 00:13:49,960
No trouble, anything else to carry up?

228
00:13:50,059 --> 00:13:51,039
I'll grab it all at once.

229
00:13:51,399 --> 00:13:51,980
Appreciate it.

230
00:13:55,759 --> 00:13:56,700
We need to worry about

231
00:13:56,700 --> 00:13:57,980
their future life.

232
00:14:05,480 --> 00:14:06,259
- Which way?
- Moving?

233
00:14:07,539 --> 00:14:08,259
It's here?

234
00:14:08,879 --> 00:14:09,659
This is the place?

235
00:14:09,860 --> 00:14:10,320
Yeah.

236
00:14:14,960 --> 00:14:16,200
Nice young man.

237
00:14:19,240 --> 00:14:20,600
Mom, Dad.

238
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:21,899
You came?

239
00:14:24,679 --> 00:14:25,720
Mr. and Mrs. Li.

240
00:14:25,779 --> 00:14:26,440
You're here.

241
00:14:26,440 --> 00:14:27,399
You should've told me.

242
00:14:27,399 --> 00:14:29,000
I'd have picked you up.

243
00:14:31,559 --> 00:14:32,639
What's all this?

244
00:14:33,120 --> 00:14:34,279
We moved to

245
00:14:34,279 --> 00:14:35,919
a bigger place.

246
00:14:36,320 --> 00:14:37,379
More comfortable.

247
00:14:37,639 --> 00:14:38,179
And

248
00:14:38,379 --> 00:14:40,120
better decor too,

249
00:14:40,200 --> 00:14:41,519
Qiao will love living here.

250
00:14:42,100 --> 00:14:42,720
Right.

251
00:14:48,059 --> 00:14:48,519
Let's go.

252
00:14:48,620 --> 00:14:49,860
Our Qiao isn't staying here.

253
00:14:50,019 --> 00:14:50,879
She's coming home with me.

254
00:14:50,980 --> 00:14:51,500
Mrs. Li.

255
00:14:51,500 --> 00:14:52,139
- Mrs. Li.
- Mom.

256
00:14:52,879 --> 00:14:53,799
Li Qiao and I

257
00:14:53,799 --> 00:14:55,679
plan to get married.

258
00:14:55,879 --> 00:14:56,500
Married?

259
00:14:56,899 --> 00:14:57,539
You don't even

260
00:14:57,539 --> 00:14:58,639
have a proper house ready.

261
00:14:58,679 --> 00:14:59,340
She won't marry you.

262
00:14:59,980 --> 00:15:00,860
You expect Qiao

263
00:15:00,919 --> 00:15:01,960
to live in a dump like this?

264
00:15:01,960 --> 00:15:03,080
Look at this place.

265
00:15:03,240 --> 00:15:03,799
It is

266
00:15:03,799 --> 00:15:04,759
a pigsty.

267
00:15:05,179 --> 00:15:06,500
Who gave you permission

268
00:15:06,980 --> 00:15:08,179
to get married?

269
00:15:09,320 --> 00:15:09,740
Let's go.

270
00:15:09,860 --> 00:15:10,279
Go.

271
00:15:10,340 --> 00:15:10,820
Boss.

272
00:15:13,139 --> 00:15:14,240
Boss, you buying a place?

273
00:15:14,679 --> 00:15:15,580
The quarterly dividends

274
00:15:15,580 --> 00:15:16,559
are in.

275
00:15:16,779 --> 00:15:18,480
With some extra from elsewhere,

276
00:15:18,860 --> 00:15:20,179
should cover a down payment.

277
00:15:21,679 --> 00:15:22,320
Who's this?

278
00:15:23,960 --> 00:15:24,700
Nice to meet you.

279
00:15:24,779 --> 00:15:25,820
I work at the pool hall,

280
00:15:26,200 --> 00:15:27,340
came to help Bo move.

281
00:15:27,679 --> 00:15:28,799
Chen Yi, come on in.

282
00:15:28,799 --> 00:15:29,600
Come inside.

283
00:15:30,340 --> 00:15:30,820
Yeah, boss.

284
00:15:31,200 --> 00:15:33,080
What did you just call him?

285
00:15:33,820 --> 00:15:34,419
Boss?

286
00:15:35,120 --> 00:15:36,200
Isn't he just the front desk guy

287
00:15:36,200 --> 00:15:36,960
at the pool hall?

288
00:15:38,240 --> 00:15:39,679
Bo didn't tell you?

289
00:15:40,139 --> 00:15:41,399
He took over the hall this quarter.

290
00:15:42,320 --> 00:15:43,000
He probably wanted to wait

291
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:44,039
till the dividends came in

292
00:15:44,159 --> 00:15:44,899
before telling you.

293
00:15:45,220 --> 00:15:46,360
Right.

294
00:15:46,720 --> 00:15:48,159
Now that the money's here,

295
00:15:48,200 --> 00:15:49,480
we can buy the place.

296
00:15:49,799 --> 00:15:51,000
Qiao and I

297
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:52,440
plan to buy this place.

298
00:15:53,100 --> 00:15:53,659
Yeah.

299
00:15:53,779 --> 00:15:54,460
He only got the confidence to tell you

300
00:15:54,460 --> 00:15:55,960
once he had money.

301
00:15:55,960 --> 00:15:56,639
Right?

